727820f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, south side, west from 75th Road, showing the thoroughfare after it was modernized. The building with the sloping roof, that looks like a church, is a fire house of the New York City Fire Department, at 75th Avenue. Shown, too, are newly-built small houses and apartment houses.
View 2 shows the same area, looking east from 73rd
Road.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: February 10, 1937
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: July 7, 1940
